OL,7,FBoth were assessing for the PM in 2009
OL,8,Fwhat action the government and Bank of
OL,9,FEngland needed to take to curb the
OL,10,Fcontinuing economic damage from the
OL,11,Fglobal financial crisis.
OL,13,FTheir assessments and recommendations
OL,14,Fwould have been highly valuable to any
OL,15,Fbank or credit institution.
OL,17,FButler, for example, in 2009 was
OL,18,Frecommending government "asset sales
OL,19,Fof even #20bn" to "relieve the debt
OL,20,Fburden, reduce borrowing costs and
OL,21,Fprovide some funds for new investment".
